**[Discussion]**
&nbsp;
**[Opinion]**
We should replace Work and Income & all benefits with a Universal Basic Income, so as to guarantee the abolition of poverty in this country, and the flexibility of work and the economy as a whole.
&nbsp;
Unlike the UBI, WINZ encourages idleness by cutting off vital payments to people who are struggling financially even after finding work. This also has the effect of worsening nationwide mental health, as well as increasing stress levels.
&nbsp;
There will always be people who refuse work. Then again, the only solution to this problem is to make work attractive, not use it as a form of punishment. There are many other reasons people choose to work, including social, moral and cultural values.
&nbsp;
It's time for 21st century politics!

I'm probably not fit enough to be leader of the NZRC, as I'm 25 years old and on disability, but I'd be more than happy to appoint somebody else for the job, so long as he/she believes in our values!
&nbsp;
Must be someone with guts, and must always speak his/her mind.
&nbsp;
**[Discuss]**

**[Opinion]**
We need to keep immigration in check.
&nbsp;
**That means letting people in based on their values, not the size of their wallets. We don't want people piggy-backing on New Zealand to get to Australia, or eroding our culture of freedom and progressiveness.**
&nbsp;
**[Discuss]**

**[Opinion]**
The only way to achieve mass-adoption of electric vehicles is simple: More government-funded research is needed to develop more affordable and efficient battery technology. This would pay off in future by reducing the cost of fuel and transportation, which means more money in the pocket for New Zealanders! 
&nbsp;
We also need to encourage bicycle / e-bike transportation by improving nation-wide cycling infrastructure, including inter-state routes. This has the benefit of reducing traffic congestion, not to mention making transportation safer for New Zealanders.
&nbsp;
**[Discuss]**

[Opinion]
There is no denying that modern life is killing us. Regardless of which religion you believe in, we have to admit that spirituality and philosophy is hugely lacking in our every day lives, not to mention academia.
&nbsp;
Our pursuit of monetary gain and the perfect career will lead us down a path of self-destruction. We need time for contemplation and self-exploration. 
&nbsp;
Know Thyself. Know the World. Know your Environment.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MEbkfAL2Tlg
&nbsp;
Technology is evolving at a steady rate, so we might just get lucky enough to be able to build this affordably.

**[Opinion]**
&nbsp;
Don't get a real job - stay at home and learn Python!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N4mEzFDjqtA
&nbsp;
..Arguably, the best use of your time. And it's free (so long as you have internet access and a PC!)
&nbsp;
Don't worry too much about bills. Educated homeless people are insanely dangerous for society. Give em' hell.. ^^

